## Repository 1

**Repository Name:**  QGIS
**Link:**  https://github.com/qgis/QGIS

### Purpose
What does this project do?
QGIS is a free, open source, cross platform (lin/win/mac) geographical information system (GIS). 

### Repository Structure
What folders or files stand out?
LAS/LAZ and EPT datasets, Python

### Documentation
How helpful is the README?
Great documentation with a lot of example pictures and really cool maps. 
Easy to follow, and good links to help and support documentation.

### Activity
Is the repository actively maintained?
Yes, looks like it is a least updated weekly sometimes more. 

### Key Observation
One thing this project does well.
Desribing the different uses for QGIS and understanding how to use and download it. 
