## Repository 2
**Repository Name:**  GRASS
**Link:**  https://github.com/OSGeo/grass

### Purpose
What does this project do?
A powerful computational engine for raster, vector, and geospatial processing. 
It supports terrain and ecosystem modeling, hydrology, data management, and imagery processing.

### Repository Structure
What folders or files stand out?
Governance.md, raster3d

### Documentation
How helpful is the README?
It was still easy to follow. A lot less documnetation than QGIS, but it does look to provide
more links to setting up outside of GitHub. 

### Activity
Is the repository actively maintained?
Yes, last edit was 2 days ago, appears to be updated weekly at least. 

### Key Observation
One thing this project does well.
Supplying helful links and focusing really on the community of GRASS, but including discorse links, 
and main contributors tabs. 
